==English==

===Verb===
'''[[suck]] [[in]]'''

# To [[cause]] someone to become slowly more and more [[involved]] in a business or situation that is often not to that person's liking.
#: ''I really didn't want to be on the committee, but somehow I got '''sucked in'''.''

===Usage notes===
* Usually used in the passive. One is '''sucked in''' by the situation.

